About AIANTA TEST

Founded in 1998, AIANTA was established by tribes for tribes to address inequities in the tourism system. Governed by an all-Native board of directors, AIANTA serves as a united voice for the $14 billion Native hospitality sector. AIANTA’s priorities are
  1. to provide technical assistance and training, research, and publications to American Indian, Alaska Native and Native Hawaiian communities engaged in tourism and hospitality;
  2. to facilitate conversations with the Native communities, federal agencies, non-profit associations, and elected officials on the economic and cultural importance of a healthy hospitality industry;
  3. to highlight the importance of visiting authentic Native destinations, including cultural, heritage, historic, and artistic sites; and
  4. to generate awareness, interest and demand for these destinations with domestic and international travelers, the travel trade and the media.
Learn more about AIANTA

About SMS

Hello. Founded in 1960, SMS Hawai'i has been spotting trends, pinpointing issues, and unlocking insights for as long as Hawai'i has been a state. Since day one, we've combined the industry's latest research and survey techniques with an insider's knowledge of Hawai'i to give clients a 360-degree view of the local issues that matter most. Our surveys get the real story on opinions and issues because we know how to talk to local people, and residents trust us with their views. As a locally owned, independent firm, we have been a trusted source of intelligence for Hawaii's business, government, and nonprofit leaders for more than six decades. From land use and housing to health and wellbeing, to the Native Hawaiian community, our studies have guided some of the most important and sensitive decisions in our state's history. In the business sphere, we provide industry-shaping research and insights in retail, tourism, shopping centers, banking, insurance, and other sectors. Cyber security has never been more critical in today's global, digital environment. That's why we are leading the way with the most up-to-date security precautions to keep your data safe. We follow best practices for data integrity, security, and privacy, and we've partnered with the Cyber Readiness Institute of Hawaii to make sure we're staying current. We also carry cyber insurance. In 2021, SMS started a new chapter with President and CEO Tim Carson at the helm. This new generation of island-born leadership is working hand-in-hand with the company's seasoned research and consulting team. Together, they combine the latest expertise with decades of experience to provide unparalleled insight into Hawai'i and the Indo-Pacific region. Learn more about SMS

About AIANTA TEST

Founded in 1998, AIANTA was established by tribes for tribes to address inequities in the tourism system. Governed by an all-Native board of directors, AIANTA serves as a united voice for the $14 billion Native hospitality sector. AIANTA’s priorities are
  1. to provide technical assistance and training, research, and publications to American Indian, Alaska Native and Native Hawaiian communities engaged in tourism and hospitality;
  2. to facilitate conversations with the Native communities, federal agencies, non-profit associations, and elected officials on the economic and cultural importance of a healthy hospitality industry;
  3. to highlight the importance of visiting authentic Native destinations, including cultural, heritage, historic, and artistic sites; and
  4. to generate awareness, interest and demand for these destinations with domestic and international travelers, the travel trade and the media.
Learn more about AIANTA

About SMS

Founded in 1960, SMS Hawai'i has been spotting trends, pinpointing issues, and unlocking insights for as long as Hawai'i has been a state. Since day one, we've combined the industry's latest research and survey techniques with an insider's knowledge of Hawai'i to give clients a 360-degree view of the local issues that matter most. Our surveys get the real story on opinions and issues because we know how to talk to local people, and residents trust us with their views. As a locally owned, independent firm, we have been a trusted source of intelligence for Hawaii's business, government, and nonprofit leaders for more than six decades. From land use and housing to health and wellbeing, to the Native Hawaiian community, our studies have guided some of the most important and sensitive decisions in our state's history. In the business sphere, we provide industry-shaping research and insights in retail, tourism, shopping centers, banking, insurance, and other sectors. Cyber security has never been more critical in today's global, digital environment. That's why we are leading the way with the most up-to-date security precautions to keep your data safe. We follow best practices for data integrity, security, and privacy, and we've partnered with the Cyber Readiness Institute of Hawaii to make sure we're staying current. We also carry cyber insurance. In 2021, SMS started a new chapter with President and CEO Tim Carson at the helm. This new generation of island-born leadership is working hand-in-hand with the company's seasoned research and consulting team. Together, they combine the latest expertise with decades of experience to provide unparalleled insight into Hawai'i and the Indo-Pacific region. Learn more about SMS
